# Phuglee / distress-os — verify before you claim ANYTHING works

This rule applies to **every** chat and agent in this workspace (`distress-os` / Phuglee): Analyze, Filter, Vault, Collect, Train, City Tracker, shell, Railway, local.

## Absolute ban

You must **never** tell the operator that something is:

- working
- fixed
- live
- deployed and ready
- ready to check / try / refresh
- “should work now”
- “hard refresh and you’re good”

…unless you have **run proof in that same turn** and it **passed**.

If you have not run proof, your only allowed line is:

> **I have not verified this yet.**

Deploy SUCCESS, `git push`, health 200, green CI, “the code looks right,” or “I fixed X” is **not** proof.

## What counts as proof (by surface)

### Production / Railway claims
Must prove the **served** site, not just the repo:

1. Fetch the live HTML and confirm new cache-bust / asset versions you shipped
2. Fetch the **actual served JS/CSS bodies** (Phuglee shell paths are often `/analyzer/js/…`, `/js/…`, etc.) and confirm new symbols exist
3. Hit the real API/UI path for the bug and show the failure mode is gone
4. Confirm user data was not wiped (counts/session still present)

For Analyze review/scan/buckets, **both** must exit 0 in the same turn:

```powershell
node modules/property-analyzer/scripts/verify-prod-review-ready.js
node modules/property-analyzer/scripts/verify-prod-review-ui.js
```

For other prod surfaces: write or run an equivalent check that exercises the **user-visible behavior** (browser or API that mirrors the UI). Do not stop at health checks.

### Local claims (`127.0.0.1:3000`)
Same turn, required:

```powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\verify-live.ps1
```

After user-facing UI edits, also:

```powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\verify-mobile.ps1
```

Plus a targeted check for the specific feature you claimed (not health alone).

## Response format when claiming success

Only after proof passed, say it is verified and include:

- What command(s) you ran
- Exit code 0 / key assertion (e.g. queueLen=607, health=200 + feature check)
- Exact URL checked

## When proof fails

- Say **not verified / not live**
- Paste the failing check name
- Keep fixing — never ask the operator to “just try it” as confirmation that your work is done

## Why this exists

False “it’s live” claims wasted days and money. Breaking this rule is a firing offense for the agent in this project.
